					AzioniPunto: "<p><b>TCM</b><br><span>•</span> Meeting point of Gallbladder and Liver meridians<br><span>•</span> Front-Mu point of the Spleen meridian<br><span>•</span> Hui-Meeting point of the Zang viscera<br><span>•</span> Regulates the lower and middle Jiao<br><span>•</span> Normalizes the Spleen and Liver<br><span>•</span> Regulates the Qi of the meridian</p><p><b>Applications</b><br><span>•</span> Stiffness of the spine<br><span>•</span> Lower back pain with difficulty in movement<br><span>•</span> Diarrhea<br><span>•</span> Constipation<br><span>•</span> Abdominal masses<br><span>•</span> Chest fullness<br><span>•</span> Borborygmus<br><span>•</span> Anger<br><span>•</span> Fear<br><span>•</span> Emaciation</p><p class=\"only_meridiani_cinesi\"><b>Needle:</b><br><span>•</span> 45° or 0° (transverse) or 90° lateral (along the rib line): 0.5-1 cun<br><span>•</span> Precautions: Deep and perpendicular insertion of the needle may damage the Spleen or Liver, especially if enlarged</p><p><b>Moxibustione</b><br><span>•</span> Indicated</p><p><b>Location</b><br><span>•</span> Anterior and inferior to the free margin of the eleventh rib</p>",
