					AzioniPunto: "<p><b>TCM</b><br><span>•</span> Meeting point of Spleen, Liver, and Yinweimai meridians<br><span>•</span> Front-Mu point of the Liver meridian<br><span>•</span> Eliminates masses<br><span>•</span> Tonifies Blood<br><span>•</span> Facilitates Qi circulation in the meridian<br><span>•</span> Normalizes the Stomach<br><span>•</span> Regulates the Liver</p><p><b>Applications</b><br><span>•</span> Epigastric pain<br><span>•</span> Acid regurgitation<br><span>•</span> Vomiting<br><span>•</span> Hiccups<br><span>•</span> Painful abdominal masses<br><span>•</span> Painful masses in the chest and lateral rib region<br><span>•</span> Heartache<br><span>•</span> Sighs<br><span>•</span> Breast distention or nodules<br><span>•</span> Chest congestion<br><span>•</span> Cough<br><span>•</span> Chest fullness</p><p class=\"only_meridiani_cinesi\"><b>Needle:</b><br><span>•</span> 90° lateral or medial: 0.5-1 cun<br><span>•</span> Precautions: Deep insertion carries the risk of pneumothorax (perforation of the pleura resulting in lung collapse)</p><p><b>Moxibustione:</b><br><span>•</span> Indicated</p><p><b>Location</b><br><span>•</span> On the vertical line of the nipple<br><span>•</span> Sixth intercostal space<br><span>•</span> 4 cun lateral to the midline of the chest</p>",
