					NomePunto: "1.ST. Chengqi (Tears Container)",
					AzioniPunto: "<p><b>TCM</b><br><span>•</span> Meeting point of <i>Stomach</i>, <i>Conception Vessel</i>, and <i>Yangqiaomai</i> meridians<br><span>•</span> Expels Wind<br><span>•</span> Clears Heat<br><span>•</span> Stops tearing<br><span>•</span> Benefits the eyes</p><p><b>Applications</b><br><span>•</span> Eye pain, redness, swelling<br><span>•</span> Visual impairment<br><span>•</span> Shortsightedness<br><span>•</span> Eye itching<br><span>•</span> Eyelid twitching<br><span>•</span> Myopia<br><span>•</span> Glaucoma<br><span>•</span> Optic neuritis<br><span>•</span> Astigmatism<br><span>•</span> Acute and chronic conjunctivitis<br></p><p class=\"only_meridiani_cinesi\"><b>Needle</b><br><span>•</span> Insert with closed eyes<br><span>•</span> Gaze upward<br><span>•</span> Push the eyeball upward<br><span>•</span> Insert slightly below first<br><span>•</span> Then perpendicularly between the eyeball and orbital ridge, 0.5-1 cun<br><span>•</span> CAUTION: Insert without manipulation<br><span>•</span> Press with a cotton ball after extraction<br><span>•</span> Use only under clinical supervision<br></p><p><b>Moxibustion</b><br><span>•</span> Contraindicated<br></p><p><b>Location</b><br><span>•</span> Forward gaze<br><span>•</span> Directly below the pupil<br><span>•</span> Between the eyeball and infraorbital rim<br></p>",
